    <item>
      <title>Better new Logs</title>
      <link>https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/changelog/2024-06-21-better-new-logs/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/changelog/2024-06-21-better-new-logs/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;We recently introduced a new Logs interface for applications in &lt;a href=&#34;https://console.clever-cloud.com&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;the Console&lt;/a&gt;, available on-demand in public beta. Since, we listened customers feedbacks and improved this feature. An updated version is now available, with two modes in the text filter field:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exact match (case-sensitive)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular expression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can select one or the other using the buttons to the right of the text field. This is only a first step, as we&amp;rsquo;ll later introduce a new stack with indexed logs to better handle such filters and provide new features.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/developers/images/changelog/new-logs-update.webp&#34; alt=&#34;New logs interface&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some of you also asked for a change of the default behavior of this Logs interface. Until now, users were redirected to &lt;code&gt;Live&lt;/code&gt; view during a deployment, otherwise to the &lt;code&gt;7 days&lt;/code&gt; view, containing all available deployments/instances, with logs of the last deployment shown. We today introduce a new mechanism and now remember the last choice of a user, per application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Depending on your feedback, we&amp;rsquo;ll improve this further in the coming weeks. Here again, this is a first step as the indexed logs will open up a wide range of possibilities in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share your comments and ideas on our &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/CleverCloud/Community/discussions/categories/new-logs-interface&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;GitHub Community&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Manage Clever Tasks in the Console</title>
      <link>https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/changelog/2024-05-28-tasks-in-console/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 May 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/changelog/2024-05-28-tasks-in-console/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;Since &lt;a href=&#34;https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/changelog/2024-04-11-clever-tools-3.5.2/&#34; &gt;its release 3.5.2&lt;/a&gt;, Clever Tools is able to manage Clever Tasks. It&amp;rsquo;s now possible to create, configure and deploy them directly from the Console. To declare an application as a Task, check the corresponding box in the &lt;code&gt;Information&lt;/code&gt; tab.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Clever Task can be run on demand. It executes the command you&amp;rsquo;ve set in the &lt;code&gt;CC_RUN_COMMAND&lt;/code&gt; environment variable, without waiting for any HTTP request on the &lt;code&gt;8080&lt;/code&gt; port. After that, the application stops. It&amp;rsquo;s just billed for the execution time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://stagingv6.cleverapps.io/developers/images/changelog/clever-tasks.webp&#34;
    alt=&#34;Defines a Clever Cloud application as a Task in Console&#34; width=&#34;800px&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Defines a Clever Cloud application as a Task in Console&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;


      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Console&#39;s components upgrade</title>
